27/07/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Free and successful local elections on 12 October would be a "key passport for integration in Europe", President Alfred Moisiu said Friday (25 July).
He said the vote would prove to the international community that Albania has finally overcome questionable practices of the past.
In other news Friday, Albania's Socialist Party decided to back incumbent Tirana Mayor Edi Rama in the local elections.
His candidacy was supported unanimously.
Also Saturday, an Albanian court sentenced the deputy governor of the country's central bank to 30 months in jail.
Dhame Pite was found guilty of favouring a French company for the printing of Albania's banknotes.
(ATA, AFP - 25/07/03)
